and communitarians alike--have disfigured much of the "republican" scholarship by falsely conjuring up a history of the United States wherein rooted and moral republicans once held sway where today we encounter uprooted and amoral liberals. Lively, stimulating, and sure to be controversial, Citizens and Citoyens is a valuable contribution to the political culture debate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aLiberalismzFrancexHistory. 0aLiberalismzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRepublicanismzFrancexHistory. 0aRepublicanismzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674274013423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674274013/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK